  "response": "The weight of an individual's arm can vary based on a number of factors, including body composition, gender, and overall size. However, on average, an arm accounts for about 5-7% of a person's total body weight. \n\nFor a person who weighs 150 pounds, the arm could weigh roughly between 7.5 to 10.5 pounds. This is a general estimate and actual weight can vary individually.",
